form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony, OMB #1115-0052

full_text: Screened by NARA, 9/21/2023 U.S Department of Justice anoitesup OMB #1115-0052 Immigration and Naturalization Service Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony Naturalization and Citizenship Branch Joof srit 300 NORTH LOS ANGELES STREET File or A # A20 258 691 LOS ANGELES, CA 90012 2/26/1993 Date You are hereby notified to appear for a Naturalization Oath Ceremony at the DATE, TIME AND PLACE SHOWN BELOW. 4/22/1993 Date YUE-TSI LEANG 12:00 Time 5422 PEMBURY DRIVE of LA PALMA C.A 90623 begindy COS ANGELES CONVENTION CENTER Place 1201 SOUTH FIGUERDA STREET LOS ANGELES, CA 90012 PROPER COURT ROOM ATTIRE IS REQUIRED HALL You must bring the following with you: This letter, with ALL of the QUESTIONS ON THE REVERSE side answered in ink or on a typewriter Alien Registration Card. Reentry Permit or Refugee Travel Document. Any immigration documents you may have. If the naturalization application is ON BEHALF OF YOUR CHILD (children), BRING your CHILD (children). f you cannot come to this ceremony, return this notice immediately and state why you cannot appear. In such case, please use the return dress in the extreme upper left hand corner of this letter. You will be sent another notice of ceremony at a later date. You must appear at oath ceremony to complete the naturalization process. m N-445A (Rev. 1/8/92) IMPORTANT - PLEASE SEE REVERSE
